      <T n="text">0x57795533<!--<font color="#199C2C"><b>Detect Emotions</b></font> can be done by selecting your Fairy Sim and looking in the Fairy Category. When Detecting Emotions, a pulse of magic will surround the Sim and temporarily display the Emotions of the nearby Sims.\n\nThe Emotions that appear are ones that can be Absorbed: Angry, Bored, Confident, Embarrassed, Energized, Flirty, Focused, Happy, Inspired, Playful, Sad, Scared, and Tense.\n\nSome Emotions cannot be Absorbed. This includes: Fine, Asleep, Dazed, Uncomfortable, and Possessed.\n\nSometimes you will see an <font color="#199C2C"><b>Exclamation Point '!'</b></font> on an Emotion when it appears. This signals that the Emotion is powerful. Powerful Emotions can be Absorbed by a Fairy, but there are serious consequences if done too much!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_FairyOccultDetectAbsorbEmotions_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:bd1ef0951cb91638</T>
      <T n="text">0x4FD5FEC5<!--<font color="#199C2C"><b>Absorbing Emotions</b></font> is the quickest and most efficient way for a Fairy Sim to regain Emotional Force!\n\nOccasionally when a Fairy Absorbs the Emotions of Another Sim they will receive a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Spillover Emotion</b></font> which matches the Emotion just absorbed.\n\nHowever, Absorbing a powerful Emotion will contribute to <font color="#199C2C"><b>Overload</b></font> in a Fairy's system. Overload starts small and accumulates as additional powerful Emotions get Absorbed.\n\nIf a Fairy becomes critically overloaded they will die, so be careful! (See <font color="#199C2C"><b>Death</b></font> Lesson)\n\nUse Detect Emotions to identify Emotions without the Exclamation Point '!' and focus on Absorbing these. This will ease the Overload, which will eventually disappear.--></T>
    </U>
